title: Birch with hoar frost in Tuntorp
description: Birch (Betula pendula) with hoar frost in winter in Tuntorp, Brastad, Lysekil Municipality, Sweden. After days of very strong winds, when all the snow was blown from trees and structures, came a few days of calm and cold weather. This formed hoar frost on all surfaces and on the third day, it had accumelated into a thick layer on everything. The only snow was on the ground, so all the "white" covering trees, plantrs and structures in the photo is hoar frost.
label: Original
